devdoc.details: A contract that can execute arbitrary calls from its owner.

executeCall(address,bytes,uint256).details: Execute an arbitrary call. Only an authority can call this.

params.value: Ether to attach to the call.

returns.resultData: The data returned by the call.

executeDelegateCall(address,bytes).details: Execute an arbitrary delegatecall, in the context of this puppet.      Only an authority can call this.

returns.resultData: The data returned by the call.

onERC1155BatchReceived(address,address,u.details: Allow this contract to receive ERC1155 tokens.

onERC1155Received(address,address,uint25.details: Allow this contract to receive ERC1155 tokens.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Signal support for receiving ERC1155 tokens.

params.interfaceID: The interface ID, as per ERC-165 rules.

returns.hasSupport: `true` if this contract supports an ERC-165 interface.

tokenFallback(address,uint256,bytes).details: Allows this contract to receive ERC223 tokens.

owner.details: Store the owner/deployer as an immutable to make this contract stateless.
